********************** Obtaining zeromq *****************************************************************
1) Obtain zeromq tar. wget http://download.zeromq.org/zeromq-3.2.2.tar.gz

2) Make sure that libtool, autoconf, automake are installed.

3) Check whether uuid-dev package, uuid/e2fsprogs RPM or equivalent on your system is installed.

4) Unpack the tar.gz source archive. tar -zxvf zeromq-3.2.2.tar.gz

5) Run ./configure, followed by make.

6) To install ØMQ system-wide run sudo make install.

7) On Linux, run sudo ldconfig after installing ØMQ.

**********************************************************************************************************
************************ Obtaining Redis *****************************************************************
1) Obtain the redis tar.gz archive. wget http://redis.googlecode.com/files/redis-2.6.9.tar.gz

2) Unpack the tar.gz source archive.  tar -xzvf redis-2.6.9.tar.gz

3) cd redis-2.6.9

4) make followed by sudo make install

**********************************************************************************************************
************************ Obtaining Protobuf **************************************************************
1) Obtain the protobuf sources. wget http://protobuf-c.googlecode.com/files/protobuf-c-0.15.tar.gz

2) Unpack the tar.gz source archive. tar -zxvf protobuf-c-0.15.tar.gz

3) cd protobuf-c

4) make followd by sudo make install


**********************************************************************************************************
****************** Installing czmq ***********************************************************************
1) Obtain the czmq from the git repo git clone git://github.com/zeromq/czmq

2) Make sure that libtool, autoconf, automake are installed.

3) Check whether uuid-dev package, uuid/e2fsprogs RPM or equivalent on your system is installed.

4) Unpack the .tar.gz source archive.

5) Run ./configure, followed by make.

6) To install ØMQ system-wide run sudo make install.

7) On Linux, run sudo ldconfig after installing CZMQ.

***********************************************************************************************************
******************* Executing the sources *****************************************************************
1) The sources has been tested over Linux platform. To compile it, execute the following command
	make build

2) The client requires two arguments, redis database IP address and Messenger Login name. To execute the client, run it as follows.

	./client <REDIS_IP> <Messenger Login>

***********************************************************************************************************


